content:
`evmone` has a basic DSL which supports formatting of (some) opcodes and outputs formatted eof containers, random example from `evmone`'s tests to give an idea:
```
deploy_container = eof_bytecode(bytecode(OP_DATALOADN) + "0040" + ret_top(), 2).data(deploy_data, deploy_data_size);
init_container = eof_bytecode(returncontract(0, 0, 32), 2).container(deploy_container);
eof_bytecode(sstore(0, eofcreate().container(0).input(0, 0).salt(Salt)) + sstore(1, 1) + OP_STOP, 4).container(init_container);
```
